<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: BOY, 11, DIES OF GUNSHOT WOUND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An 11-year-old South El Monte boy died after he was accidently shot Friday 
afternoon while playing with a rifle at a friend's home, coroners officials 
said. 
</P>
<P>
The boy, Salvador Ortiz, died Saturday at Greater El Monte Community Hospital 
after receiving a single bullet wound to the head, said Claude Boucher, the 
coroner's supervising investigator. 
</P>
<P>
Ortiz and a 14-year-old friend, whose name was not released because of his age, 
came across a .22-caliber rifle that they did not realize was loaded, sheriff's 
deputies said. 
</P>
<P>
The 14-year-old boy began handling the gun and when he pulled the trigger, the 
gun fired once, striking Ortiz in the head, deputies said. 
</P>
<P>
Neither the 14-year-old nor two other boys playing in the house were hurt, 
deputies said. Sheriff's homicide detectives declared it an accidental 
shooting. 
</P>
<P>
Deputies said they did not know whether either parent was home at the time. 
</P>
</TEXT>
