<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: FUND ESTABLISHED TO AID HOMELESS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Help the Homeless Help Themselves Inc., a Palos Verdes Peninsula group that 
raises money for organizations assisting the homeless, has established a 
permanent $20,000 fund for low-interest loans to help working families pay rent 
and utilities, according to the group's president, Bill Finkel. 
</P>
<P>
"This is for those who earn too little to pay first or last month's rent, so 
they will not be homeless," said Finkel, a Rancho Palos Verdes resident who 
founded the group in 1987. 
</P>
<P>
Finkel said any shelter may refer people to the group and individuals also may 
apply. More information is available from Finkel at (213) 377-3213. 
</P>
</TEXT>
