EYESORE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Driving south from Santa Barbara recently, my husband and I happened by Zuma 
Beach, and there I was confronted by an eyesore that broke my heart. 
</P>
<P>
The beach was almost deserted -- yet the bright orange and white trash cans 
that proliferated (one almost every 20 feet) were enough to blight the 
landscape and make me want to cry. 
</P>
<P>
Were a private developer to permit such an atrocity, he would be skewered by 
the public, but the "public" beach is scenically and environmentally destroyed 
by this outrageous condition. 
</P>
<P>
Certainly our taxes, bond issues, etc. should pay for trash cans that are not 
so aesthetically out of line! 
</P>
<P>
CAROL KIESSIG 
