<P>
Anti-apartheid pressure has caused the black U.S. pop group the Commodores to 
cancel the concerts they planned to give next month in South Africa. A 
spokeswoman said Monday that the group pulled out after "slurs on their 
intentions" by U.S. and South African groups.ALEENE MacMINN 
