<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: WESTMINSTER; 
</P>
<P>
FIRE DAMAGES HOME; WOMAN ESCAPES UNHURT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A fast-moving fire heavily damaged a home Monday, but a woman at first believed 
to be trapped inside escaped unhurt, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
The fire destroyed much of the garage and kitchen area of the home in the 14800 
block of Yarborough Street, Westminster Fire Department Battalion Chief Don 
Herr said. 
</P>
<P>
When the fire broke out about 3:40 p.m., a woman who was in the kitchen 
apparently made her way safely out a back door to a nearby school. 
</P>
<P>
The blaze's cause remained under investigation. Damage to the residence was 
estimated at $100,000, fire officials said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
