<P>
KENNEDY'S HANSELL SIGNS WITH RED SOX 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Greg Hansell, The Times' Orange County player of the year in baseball, said he 
has signed a contract with the Boston Red Sox. 
</P>
<P>
Hansell will report Thursday to Winter Haven, Fla., the club's Class-A team in 
the Florida State League. 
</P>
<P>
Hansell, who helped lead Kennedy High School to the Southern Section 3-A 
baseball championship, had 123 strikeouts in 96 innings, a 13-1 record and a 
1.24 earned-run average. 
</P>
<P>
Hansell had signed a national letter of intent to play football at Nevada Reno 
in the fall. 
</P>
