<P>
3 SANTA ANA MEN HELD IN IDA. ROBBERY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and wire service reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Three Santa Ana men, reputedly members of a Vietnamese gang known as the "Santa 
Ana Boys," were arrested late Monday for the brutal robbery of a Boise, Ida., 
community center, during which a woman was repeatedly pistol-whipped. 
</P>
<P>
Hien Thuong Nguyen, 24; Trung Quang Nguyen, 20, and Thanh Ban Nguyen, 26, who 
are not related, are suspects in a June 17 robbery which netted $29,000 in cash 
and jewelry. The three men were arrested in Santa Ana after 11 p.m. Monday by 
Westminster and Boise investigators, Westminster police spokesman Tom Broderson 
said. 
</P>
<P>
During the robbery a 48-year-old woman was beaten to force her to reveal the 
location of additional jewelry. An extradition warrant has been issued, and the 
suspects are being held in Orange County Jail. 
</P>
</TEXT>
