<P>
ARAFAT HAS UNSCHEDULED CHINA STOP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and wire service reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
TUNIS, Tunisia 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Palestine Liberation Organization leader Yasser Arafat flew to Vietnam en route 
to Cambodia today after an emergency landing and unscheduled 18-hour stopover 
in Beijing, a PLO spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
"The chairman arrived in Hanoi this minute," PLO spokesman Ahmed Abdel Rahman 
said by telephone. "I just spoke to him on the telephone. He is 100% safe." 
Abdel Rahman said Arafat's chartered airplane made an "emergency landing" in 
Beijing because of "aviation problems" while en route from North Korea to 
Cambodia, but the nature of the problem was not specified. 
</P>
</TEXT>
