<HEADLINE>
<P>
NAMES IN THE NEWS; 
</P>
<P>
JOHNSON, GRIFFITH TIE KNOT -- AGAIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ASPEN, Colo. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Don Johnson and Melanie Griffith, whose marriage 13 years ago ended less than a 
year later, exchanged vows a second time in a low-key ceremony held at the 
actor's mountainside ranch, their publicist said today. 
</P>
<P>
Johnson, 39, the former star of the television series "Miami Vice," and 
Griffith, 31, nominated for an Academy Award for "Working Girl," were married 
Monday evening in the woods near Johnson's ranch at Little Woody Creek, an 
exclusive community 10 miles northwest of Aspen, said Elliot Mintz, publicist 
for both celebrities. 
</P>
<P>
Johnson and Griffith, daughter of actress Tippi Hedren, are expecting their 
first child, a girl, in early October. Johnson's parents and Hedren, star of 
the Hitchcock film, "The Birds," attended the wedding. 
</P>
</TEXT>
