<P>
ON THE SIDELINES; 
</P>
<P>
PARILLI NAMED DYNAMITE COACH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
DENVER 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Babe Parilli, who played quarterback in the NFL and old AFL and has coached in 
the pro ranks as well, has been named head coach of the Denver Dynamite of the 
Arena Football League. Parilli, a resident of Denver since he was the 
quarterback coach for the Broncos from 1977 to 1979, said Monday he is 
optimistic about the Dynamite, the 1987 champion and a non-contender last 
season. Parilli coached the New England entry in the Arena League last season. 
